title: For Sale:   EoTech 553/ SU-231/PEQ
postcontent:
This is the model (SU-231/PEQ) EoTech that the Special Operations Command standardized as the optic used for close quarter and urban combat.
The two features that set it apart from the others are the night vision mode and the integrated quick detach/attach A.R.M.S. levers. Being skeptical of its ability to return to zero after being removed, I tested this extensively when I purchased it and at 100 yards I was never able to detect a point of impact shift. Due to the EoTech having the dot within a 65 MOA circle reticle nothing is faster on targets up close.  I have found that I am able to quickly and easily hit a 10" plate offhand at 300 yards with the central 1 MOA dot (match ammo in a 1/2 minute capable rifle holding 4-6 inches over with a 50 yard zero). The sight is in very good condition since it has lived most of its life in a rifle case inside of a safe. It has a very light barely noticeable scrape on the side of the hood and the buttons indicate that it has been lightly used.  I have decided to put a dedicated magnified optic on this rifle due to its accuracy and have no other rifle on which it can be used.

These sights sell for $700 new. $500 is my price and I believe that it is very reasonable. If you are thinking about a lowball offer don't wast your time, I will not respond. This is a face to face sell only in the North Alabama area, I will not ship. I am not generally not interested in a trade but I have been offered items in the past that have changed my mind. Typically I respond quickly to your email but at times due to my erratic schedule it may be the following day.
